  "text": "Participants completed an interviewer-administered questionnaire, including demographic, clinical, medication use, and dietary and supplementation information at baseline and at each of the four annual follow-up visits. Modified Food Frequency Questionnaires (FFQ) and 4-day food records [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] were also completed at these visits. Those reporting regular nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) use at all five visits were coded as 'regular users'.",
